# Expense Sharing App

A simple web application for managing shared expenses among friends. This app allows users to sign up, log in, add friends, record expenses, and view balances.

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

## Features

- User authentication (sign up, log in, log out)
- Add and manage friends
- Record expenses
- View recorded expenses
- View balances shared with friends

## Installation

Follow these steps to set up the project on your local machine:

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.x
- `pip` (Python package installer)

### Step 1: Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/expense-sharing-app.git
cd expense-sharing-app
```

### Step 2: Create a Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`
```

### Step 3: Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install Flask Flask-SQLAlchemy Flask-Login Werkzeug
```

## Usage

### Step 1: Run the Application

```bash
python app.py
```

### Step 2: Open in Browser

Open your browser and go to `http://127.0.0.1:5000/`.

### Application Routes

- `/signup`: User sign up
- `/login`: User log in
- `/logout`: User log out
- `/index`: Home page showing friends
- `/add`: Add an expense
- `/view`: View recorded expenses
- `/balances`: View shared balances
- `/add_friend`: Add a friend

## Project Structure

```plaintext
expense-sharing-app/
├── static/
│   └── styles.css         # External CSS file
├── templates/
│   ├── base.html          # Base template with sidebar
│   ├── signup.html        # Sign up page
│   ├── login.html         # Login page
│   ├── index.html         # Home page
│   ├── add_expense.html   # Add expense page
│   ├── view_expenses.html # View expenses page
│   ├── balances.html      # View balances page
│   └── add_friend.html    # Add friend page
├── app.py                 # Main application file
└── expense_sharing.db     # SQLite database (auto-generated)
```

